Popular recording artist and music producer, Larry Gaaga has entered the battle for one of the categories at the 2022 AMVCAs. Larry Gaaga was revealed as one of the nominees in the category for his work on the soundtrack of Ramsey Nouah’s ‘Rattlesnake: The Ahanna Story.’ This has put the hitmaker on the same platform to win a sum of N1 million, which has been tied to the award category.   Chocolate City’s signee, Noon Dave debuts with Brunch     AMAA partners StarTimes to reward filmmakers at 2022 short…     Michael O: singing for Obama has been a blessing   Pepsi, the tactical sponsor to 2022 AMVCAs, announced that it will be celebrating the winner of the Best Soundtrack category with a special prize of N1 million amidst other gifts. Also on the same platform to contest the winning prize with Larry Gaaga are Boumeester Lindsay and Kagwe Mungai for ‘Just In Time,’ Dabs Awom for ‘Amina,’ Michael Pulse and Ponti Dikuua for ‘The White Line,’ Awele Mekwunye and Bizzouch for ‘ Light In the Dark,’ Pascal Aka and Raquel for ‘Gold Coast Lounge,’ and producers of Collision Course for ‘Collision Course.’ The awards ceremony is billed for Saturday, May 14, 2022, in Lagos, Nigeria.